# Run gate commands once

Heavy gates (`pnpm test:packages`, `test:integration`, `build`, `lint`, `fixtures:check`, `turbo typecheck`) take ~30s–3min. Re-running them to extract a different output slice is the largest waste of agent time in this repo.

## Do

Run once, capture full output and exit code, then read/grep the file:

```bash
mkdir -p wip
pnpm test:packages > wip/test-packages.log 2>&1; echo "exit=$?" >> wip/test-packages.log
grep -E " FAIL |Test Files" wip/test-packages.log
```

After a failure, re-run **just the failing file**, not the whole suite:

```bash
pnpm --filter @prisma-next/cli test test/commands/migration-list-json-golden.test.ts
```

For programmatic consumption, use a structured reporter on the first run:

```bash
pnpm test:packages --reporter=json --outputFile=wip/test-packages.json
```

## Don't

- Pipe the gate directly to `tail`/`grep`/`head` — discards the rest of the output *and* hides the exit code (tail/grep return 0).
- Re-run the suite to refine a filter. Grep the log on disk instead.
- Pass `--force` to `turbo` reflexively. Only force when a concrete cache-staleness reason applies this run (e.g. just edited `tsconfig.json`/lockfile).

If a pipe is unavoidable, preserve the exit code with `${PIPESTATUS[0]}` or `set -o pipefail`.
